🧩 Recover Palindrome
💡 Idea
A palindrome is uniquely determined only if every position is forced.
Check:

For every pair (i, n-i-1):
If both are '?' → ❌ multiple choices → NO
If n is odd:
If middle is '?' → ❌ multiple choices → NO

Otherwise → ✅ YES

✅ Java Solution
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int t = sc.nextInt();

        while (t-- > 0) {
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            String s = sc.next();

            boolean unique = true;

            // Check mirrored pairs
            for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) {
                if (s.charAt(i) == '?' && s.charAt(n - i - 1) == '?') {
                    unique = false;
                    break;
                }
            }

            // Check middle character (for odd length)
            if (n % 2 == 1 && s.charAt(n / 2) == '?') {
                unique = false;
            }

            System.out.println(unique ? "YES" : "NO");
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}
🧠 Summary
?? pair → NO
middle ? (odd length) → NO
otherwise → YES

